# Next.js app patterns

## Route groups

- `(application)` — authenticated layout with sidebar
- `(login)` — public auth pages
- `(admin)` — patstore platform admin only

## Layout pattern

Both apps fetch the current user server-side in `layout.tsx` via Parse REST (`users/me`), then pass to `LayoutContext`.

Client providers differ:
- **patflow**: `PatflowAppContextProvider`, `NotificationContextProvider`
- **patstore**: `PatstoreAppContextProvider` (requires active project)

## Client vs server

- Add `"use client"` only when using hooks, state, or browser APIs
- Keep `page.tsx` as re-exports when possible (no `"use client"` needed)
- API routes use `export const runtime = "edge"`

## Styling

- Global styles: `@repo/styles/global`, `@repo/styles/layout`
- Component styles: co-located `.module.scss` or `.scss`
- Use existing UI classes (`full_button`, `layout`, etc.) before adding new ones

## Imports

```tsx
import { SomeModule } from "@repo/modules";
import { useFindData, useAppContext } from "@repo/provider";
import { SomeType } from "@repo/types";
import { Table, Sidebar } from "@repo/ui";
```
